              <td class="p-4 text-yellow-400">One by one</td>
              <td class="p-4 text-green-400">Excellent (Playlists)</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-white/5">
              <td class="p-4 font-bold text-slate-300">Safety</td>
              <td class="p-4 text-green-400">Sandboxed in Browser</td>
              <td class="p-4 text-red-400">Risk of Malware</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
      <p>
        For most users downloading individual songs, an online converter is safer and faster. You aren't giving a random .exe file permission to run on your computer. You're just downloading a passive .mp3 file.
      </p>

      <!-- SAFETY CHECKLIST -->
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mt-16 mb-6">The Safety Checklist: How to spot a Scam Site</h2>
      <p>
        The internet is the Wild West. Here are 3 red flags to watch out for when trying other converters:
      </p>
      <ul class="space-y-4 list-none pl-0">
        <li class="flex gap-4 items-start bg-red-900/10 p-4 rounded-lg">
          <span class="text-red-500 font-bold text-xl">1.</span>
          <div>
            <strong class="text-white block">Requests to Enable Notifications</strong>
            <span class="text-slate-400 text-sm">Never, ever click "Allow" on notification popups. This is how spam sites bombard your desktop with ads for gambling and fake antivirus software.</span>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="flex gap-4 items-start bg-red-900/10 p-4 rounded-lg">
          <span class="text-red-500 font-bold text-xl">2.</span>
          <div>
            <strong class="text-white block">Needs an Extension</strong>
            <span class="text-slate-400 text-sm">If a site asks you to install a Chrome Extension just to download an MP3, run away. Extensions have full access to your browsing history and data.</span>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="flex gap-4 items-start bg-red-900/10 p-4 rounded-lg">
          <span class="text-red-500 font-bold text-xl">3.</span>
          <div>
            <strong class="text-white block">Required Sign-Up</strong>
            <span class="text-slate-400 text-sm">Converting a public video should not require your email address. If they ask for it, they are likely selling it to marketing lists.</span>
          </div>
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p class="mt-4 text-green-400 font-bold">
        ‚úÖ Convert2MP3 passes all these tests. No notifications, no extensions, no sign-ups.
      </p>

      <!-- SAFETY & TROUBLESHOOTING -->
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mt-16 mb-6">Troubleshooting: When Things Go Wrong</h2>
      <p>
        Technology is great... until it isn't. If you hit a snag, don't panic. Here are the most common hiccups users face and how to fix them instantly.
      </p>

      <div class="space-y-6">
        <details class="bg-slate-800/30 rounded-xl p-4 group open:bg-slate-800/50 transition-colors cursor-pointer">
            <summary class="font-bold text-lg text-white list-none flex justify-between items-center">
                <span>üö´ "Error: Video Not Found"</span>
                <span class="text-violet-400 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform">‚ñº</span>
            </summary>
            <div class="mt-4 text-slate-400 pl-4 border-l-2 border-violet-500/20">
                <p><strong>The Fix:</strong> Check if the video is "Private" or "Age Restricted". Our servers (and any legal tool) cannot access content that requires a login. Try opening the link in an Incognito window‚Äîif you can watch it there, we can convert it.</p>
