            </summary>
            <div class="mt-4 text-slate-400 pl-4 border-l-2 border-violet-500/20">
                <p><strong>Yes!</strong> But iOS is tricky with downloads. We recommend using our <strong>"Add to Home Screen"</strong> feature to install Convert2MP3 as a web app. Once converted, your file will usually land in the "Files" app on your iPhone. From there, you can play it or share it via AirDrop.</p>
            </div>
        </details>
      </div>

      <!-- CONCLUSION -->
      <div class="mt-20 p-8 bg-gradient-to-br from-violet-900/40 to-slate-900 rounded-3xl border border-violet-500/20 text-center">
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Ready to Build Your Library?</h3>
        <p class="text-slate-400 mb-8">
            Now that you're armed with knowledge, it's time to start your collection.
        </p>
        <a href="/" class="inline-block bg-white text-violet-900 hover:bg-violet-100 px-8 py-4 rounded-xl font-bold uppercase tracking-wide shadow-lg shadow-white/10 transition-transform transform hover:-translate-y-1">
            Start Converting Now
        </a>
      </div>

      <!-- ARTICLE SCHEMA -->
      <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
        "@context": "https://schema.org",
        "@type": "Article",
        "headline": title,
        "description": description,
        "image": [
            "https://convert2mp3.online/og-image.jpg"
        ],
        "datePublished": publishDate,
        "dateModified": new Date().toISOString(),
        "author": [{
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Convert2MP3 Team",
            "url": "https://convert2mp3.online"
        }]
      })} />
    </article>
  </main>
  
  <Footer />
</Layout>
